Hi there!

About Me

I am Nevin Ada Çakmak, a 2nd year Computer Science student at the University of Toronto, in Information Systems stream which also imparts an appreciation of the CS's transformative impact on science and society. My passion lies in the intersection of technology and human learning, and I am committed to promoting gender equality in STEM fields. With over seven years of experience in FIRST robotics programs, I have served as a member, team lead, and mentor.

My technical skills include proficiency in C, Python, Java, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. I am actively engaged in the tech community, holding leadership roles such as Vice President of Operations for the Data Science & Statistics Society ds3utsc.com and Co-Founder & Co-President of C.R.E.A.T.E. at UTSC.
